name: NamedNodeMap
description: The NamedNodeMap interface represents a collection of Attr objects. Objects inside a NamedNodeMap are not in any particular order, unlike NodeList, although they may be accessed by an index as in an array.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.length
members.description: Returns the amount of objects in the map.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.getNamedItem()
members.description: Returns a Attr, corresponding to the given name.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.setNamedItem()
members.description: Replaces, or adds, the Attr identified in the map by the given name.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.removeNamedItem()
members.description: Removes the Attr identified by the given map.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.item()
members.description: Returns the Attr at the given index, or null if the index is higher or equal to the number of nodes.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.getNamedItemNS()
members.description: Returns a Attr identified by a namespace and related local name.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.setNamedItemNS()
members.description: Replaces, or adds, the Attr identified in the map by the given namespace and related local name.

members.name: NamedNodeMap.removeNamedItemNS()
members.description: Removes the Attr identified by the given namespace and related local name.
